</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="112" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1074,595,681]" pageId="5" pageNumber="112">
DISTRIBUTION AND NATURAL HISTORY: The species is apparently restricted to 
<collectingCountry box="[151,270,626,649]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="5" pageNumber="112">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, where it was collected at elevations ranging from 
<quantity box="[804,946,626,649]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="112" unit="m" value="1500.0" valueMax="1600.0" valueMin="1400.0">1400-1600 m</quantity>
using flight intercept traps.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="112" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1074,700,786]" pageId="5" pageNumber="112">
COMMENTS: From the Neotropical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Curtis" authorityYear="1829" box="[637,764,700,723]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[637,764,700,723]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="112">Megarthrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possessing a conspicuous humeral callus (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuccodoro &amp; C. &amp; P. &amp; Ch-" authorityYear="2011" box="[324,432,732,755]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bierigi">
<emphasis box="[324,432,732,755]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="112">M. bierigi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bierig" authorityYear="1940" box="[446,593,732,755]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inaequalis">
<emphasis box="[446,593,732,755]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="112">M. inaequalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bierig" authorityYear="1940" box="[646,797,732,755]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mammiger">
<emphasis box="[646,797,732,755]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="112">M. mammiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuccodoro &amp; C. &amp; P. &amp; Ch-" authorityYear="2011" box="[820,927,732,755]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bierigi">
<emphasis box="[820,927,732,755]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="112">M. bierigi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily distinguished by its lack of elytral discal humps. See comments under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bierig" authorityYear="2011" box="[909,1042,763,786]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adelphus">
<emphasis box="[909,1042,763,786]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="112">M. adelphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
